</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Introduction</title><p class="- topic/p ">The PBA measures the relative humidity (RH) and temperature of the environmental air. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The relative humidity is defined as the ratio of water vapor in the air at a given temperature to the maximum amount which could exist at that temperature. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The temperature measured by the PBA is used to determine the optimal settings for the keep-healthy mode. This sensor is also used to adapt the print surface temperature to prevent condensation. 
